title: Stevenage 2-1 Wycombe: Match Report
text: Stevenage 2-1 Wycombe: Match Report 17 Oct 2015 16:32:00 Goalkeeper Jesse Joronen scores to help Stevenage to victoryGoalkeeper Jesse Joronen scored an amazing first-half goal as Stevenage claimed a 2-1 win against Wycombe.Joronen's long punt upfield was misjudged by opposite number Matt Ingram with the ball bouncing over his head and into the net to leave Boro fans jubilant after 10 minutes.Wycombe grew into the game as the half went on but did not create anything of note and just before half-time Stevenage striker Armand Gnanduillet stooped low to head Jerome Okimo's centre onto the crossbar.The home side started the second half the better and their early pressure was rewarded after a corner from the left was met by Gnanduillet, who finished with a thumping header.Wycombe were struggling to create chances but substitute Michael Harriman was integral in their consolation goal as his delightful right-foot cross was met with aplomb by Max Kretzschmar.Wycombe piled forward in the closing stages as they looked desperately for an equaliser but could not muster any clear-cut opportunities.Southampton loanee Jason McCarthy could only head over from a left-wing cross and Harriman shot high and wide.
